decision_conditions:
Condition : 3 - No development above ground level shall take place until full details of all materials to be used in the construction of the external surfaces of the development hereby permitted have been submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority. Details must include a detailed schedule of materials and rendered drawings to illustrate how all external materials will appear together.
Details shall include:
i.	Brick/stonework (including brick, stone, masonry, brick framing features) including all mortar colours, joint type, brick bond;
ii.	Cladding materials, including for the cycle/refuse stores
iii.	Tiles / roof covering; including parapet coping / capping materials, dormers and canopies, and green roofs for cycle/refuse stores;
iv.	Window types and reveals / sills / head details 
v.	Balcony details (including soffits, panels and frame);
vi.	All privacy measures (including obscure glazing details, privacy screens etc.);
vii.	Balustrading treatment (including details / sections / materials)
viii.	Any other materials / details / fittings to be used (including solar panels, extract vents, rainwater goods, boiler flues etc.)
The development shall then be carried out in accordance with the approved details and maintained as such thereafter.
